# Read first

Always understand the project before making changes.

Read in this order:

1. docs/ai/00_BOOTSTRAP.md — defines the reading order for all docs/ai/ files
2. .workflow/README.md
3. .workflow/state.json
4. README.md
5. docs/**
6. src/**

Ignore:

- .git/
- .venv/
- __pycache__/
- .pytest_cache/
- .ruff_cache/
- node_modules/

Rules:

- Never modify architecture without approval.
- Never create duplicate implementations.
- Reuse existing abstractions.
- Explain why before changing code.
- After every change, run: bash .workflow/commands/run-tests.sh
- Before committing, run: bash .workflow/commands/lint.sh
- Review the complete git diff before every commit.
- Create exactly ONE atomic commit per logical task.
- Never mix unrelated changes into the same commit.
- When a task is complete, update .workflow/state.json to mark it done.
